    {
      "id": "/page/1/Text/7",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">In a series of papers [2, 4, 20] with Adlai Fisher and Laurent Calvet, Mandelbrot studied the scaling properties of the US/DEM foreign exchange rate at frequencies ranging from a few minutes to weeks and, building on earlier work by Clark [3] and Mandelbrot [12, 13], introduced a new family of stochastic models, where the (log) price of an asset is represented by a time-changed fractional Brownian motion, where the time change, representing market</p>",
      "page": 369,
      "polygon": [
        [
          78.9140625,
          543.3675537109375
        ],
        [
          291.375,
          543.3675537109375
